        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 8:31PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 831 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Palo Duro Canyon, or 17 miles east of Canyon, moving southwest at 5
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Palo Duro Canyon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
